erary scene that threatened the authenticity of the poetic calling. He shows how modernist debuts evoke markedly idiosyncratic paths, while postwar first books evoke trajectories that balance professional imperatives with traditional literary ideals. Debut titles ranging from Simpson's The Arrivistes to Ken Chen's Juvenilia stress the strikingly pervasive theme of beginning, accommodating a new demand for career development even as it distances the poets from that demand.Combining literary analysis with cultural history, The First Book will interest scholars and students of twentieth-century literature as well as readers and writers of poetry.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Mai 2019) 0aAmerican poetryy20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aAuthorship. 0aPoets, Americany20th century. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Poetry.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPUP eBook-Package Pilot Project 2014-2015z978311044418608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPUP eBook-Package Pilot Project 2014-2015z978311066592540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781400873791zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781400873791.jpg  a978-3-11-044418-6  PUP eBook-Package Pilot Project 2014-2015  a978-3-11-066592-5  PUP eBook-Package Pilot Project 2014-2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG  aPDA9PRIN